that blocks
the electrical signals

21:07.400 --> 21:08.635
that are read by Teeps.

21:08.668 --> 21:10.437
It seems our "Hood Maker"
has access

21:10.470 --> 21:12.605
to Science Division
level technology.

21:12.639 --> 21:14.707
I want a list of all
Union Science Divisions.

21:14.741 --> 21:18.478
I want to know what they make,
how they make them, who for.

21:18.511 --> 21:20.347
Don't just look at me.
Go and be a detective.

21:20.380 --> 21:22.582
There may be more of these
things hitting the streets.

21:22.615 --> 21:23.950
They're powerful,
and they work.

21:23.983 --> 21:26.319
OFFICER:
Maybe that's a good thing.

21:26.353 --> 21:27.487
Who said that?

21:28.721 --> 21:29.956
You've been out there.

21:29.989 --> 21:31.958
It's piano-wire tight.

21:31.991 --> 21:34.794
We could lose control
of this city.

21:34.827 --> 21:36.896
Normals are looking for a way
to fight back

21:36.929 --> 21:38.931
against the Anti-Immunity Bill,
and this is it.

21:38.965 --> 21:40.967
And that division?
That's only gonna get worse.

21:41.000 --> 21:42.369
Sorry, sir.

21:42.402 --> 21:44.704
How can I be
of assistance

21:44.737 --> 21:46.973
in this investigation,
Agent Ross?

21:50.743 --> 21:52.745
Information.

21:52.779 --> 21:55.415
Unbleached waxed
linen material.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.117
Waxed linen.

21:58.150 --> 22:01.988
[ECHOING]
Linen, linen, linen.

22:02.021 --> 22:03.956
[DISTORTED VOICES WHISPERING]

22:07.460 --> 22:09.896
[***]

22:21.140 --> 22:23.610
[VOICES OVERLAPPING]

22:28.615 --> 22:30.550
[VOICES SWELLING]

22:33.986 --> 22:35.655
[VOICES STOP]

22:35.688 --> 22:37.790
Okay, here it is.

22:39.191 --> 22:41.661
Waxed linen thread
is a cellulose fiber.

22:41.694 --> 22:43.563
Its weft yarns
are arranged to make it

22:43.596 --> 22:45.097
light, breathable,
and tough.

22:45.131 --> 22:48.735
Its use today is primarily
in the clothing industry,

22:48.768 --> 22:51.103
especially in manufacture
of quality clothing.

22:51.137 --> 22:53.406
But also traditionally
in bookbinding.

22:53.440 --> 22:54.974
There are eight
fabric outlets

22:55.007 --> 22:57.710
that I can find
in the Inner City Area.

22:57.744 --> 22:59.679
Ah...

22:59.712 --> 23:00.880
I'll write them down
for you.

23:00.913 --> 23:02.615
ROSS:
I love a partner

23:02.649 --> 23:04.651
that gets things done.
Don't you?

23:04.684 --> 23:06.453
I want these
outlets visited.

23:06.486 --> 23:09.088
Let's find the Hood Maker
before this thing runs amuck.

23:09.121 --> 23:11.858
[GOATS BLEATING]

23:11.891 --> 23:14.694
[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

23:14.727 --> 23:17.497
[***]

23:22.168 --> 23:24.771
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

23:24.804 --> 23:26.973
CHILD 1:
Hey, over here. Over here!

23:34.246 --> 23:35.582
CHILD 2:
Hey, look!

23:43.055 --> 23:44.190
[DOG BARKING]

23:53.500 --> 23:55.735
We're not
making friends.

23:55.768 --> 24:00.773
Nope. But we are
influencing people.

24:00.807 --> 24:03.743
[VOICES WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY]

24:08.815 --> 24:10.617
What did you say to them?

24:10.650 --> 24:11.818
Nothing, they're just--

24:11.851 --> 24:15.488
Kids showing off.

24:15.522 --> 24:16.889
Is it noisy in there?

24:16.923 --> 24:19.726
Yeah. It can be.

24:19.759 --> 24:21.861
You learn to filter.

24:23.696 --> 24:25.832
Harder in the city, though.

24:25.865 --> 24:28.901
I'd like to go away
some day.

24:28.935 --> 24:30.603
Where to?

24:34.907 --> 24:36.175
What?

24:37.977 --> 24:40.079
It's funny.

24:40.112 --> 24:41.814
Being around you
is different.

24:43.550 --> 24:44.717
"Different"? How so?

24:44.751 --> 24:45.985
[CHILDREN YELLING]

24:46.018 --> 24:47.219
Go home, Teep.

24:47.253 --> 24:48.955
Oi! Manners!

24:48.988 --> 24:51.190
Get back here,
and apologize to the lady.

24:51.223 --> 24:53.259
Hey, you? Come here.
Come here, you.

24:53.292 --> 24:56.629
[***]

24:56.663 --> 24:58.297
MARY:
Help me.

24:58.330 --> 25:01.768
Help me. Help me.

25:01.801 --> 25:02.969
[GASPS]

25:03.002 --> 25:05.004
[DISTORTED]:
Help me!

25:05.037 --> 25:07.940
Honor?

25:07.974 --> 25:09.241
MARY:
Help me!

25:22.354 --> 25:23.723
ROSS:
Out the way!

25:23.756 --> 25:25.558
[***]

25:25.592 --> 25:27.126
MARY: Help me.
Where are we?

25:27.159 --> 25:29.195
MARY [WHISPERING]:
Help me.

25:29.228 --> 25:31.163
[GASPING]

25:32.231 --> 25:33.633
[VOICE LAUGHING]

25:33.666 --> 25:35.134
ROSS:
Clearance!
Drop your weapon!

25:35.167 --> 25:37.036
MAN:
So I'll think of
a playing card--

25:37.069 --> 25:38.237
MARY:
Help me.

25:38.270 --> 25:39.639
MAN:
--and she has to tell me

25:39.672 --> 25:41.007
what it is.
Help me.

25:41.040 --> 25:43.009
Bet I win.
ROSS: Let her go.

25:43.042 --> 25:44.243
It's gonna be
all right, Mary.

25:44.276 --> 25:46.278
He made me read him,
and it hurt.

25:46.312 --> 25:47.880
She tried.

25:47.914 --> 25:49.982
Really hard.

25:50.016 --> 25:52.084
But she couldn't even
scratch the surface.

25:52.118 --> 25:53.285
Drop the gun. Now.

25:53.319 --> 25:54.687
MAN:
So she hit me.

25:54.721 --> 25:57.023
Ah. She hit me.

25:57.056 --> 25:59.291
I'm not just a Normal.

25:59.325 --> 26:01.027
I'm Free Union.

26:01.060 --> 26:03.663
I'm important,
you Teep bitch.

26:03.696 --> 26:05.698
[MAN LAUGHING]

26:05.732 --> 26:07.800
[***]

26:11.203 --> 26:13.239
[IMITATING GUN FIRE]

26:13.272 --> 26:15.642
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

26:18.745 --> 26:20.379
I'm Director of
Federal Resources.

26:20.412 --> 26:21.981
You can't keep me.

26:22.014 --> 26:23.783
ROSS:
Yeah, you're
an important man.

26:23.816 --> 26:25.652
Did you know it's illegal
for important men

26:25.685 --> 26:26.953
to visit places
like this?

26:26.986 --> 26:29.288
Trust me. We can
hold you long enough.

26:29.321 --> 26:30.757
Well, these girls,

26:30.790 --> 26:32.124
they don't care
about politics.

26:32.158 --> 26:34.293
They dig out your dreams
for a few quid.

26:34.326 --> 26:35.695
And here's the best bit:

26:35.728 --> 26:37.797
They can't fake it.

26:37.830 --> 26:38.998
[LAUGHS]

26:39.031 --> 26:41.000
But out there...

26:41.033 --> 26:42.969
we have to protect
ourselves.

26:43.002 --> 26:46.238
That's why we've got
to have those hoods.

26:46.272 --> 26:48.307
Eh? Heh, heh.

26:48.340 --> 26:50.276
She's sweet.
Stop it.

26:50.309 --> 26:51.944
D-- Oh...

26:51.978 --> 26:53.345
Oh, dear.

26:53.379 --> 26:54.747
[LAUGHS]

26:54.781 --> 26:56.115
You know, it's not the hoods

26:56.148 --> 26:57.917
you got to worry
about, agent.

26:57.950 --> 26:59.686
It's the Teeps.

26:59.719 --> 27:02.722
There's an underground.
They're ready to rise up.

27:02.755 --> 27:04.657
You can't trust any of them.

27:04.691 --> 27:07.827
Especially the ones
you like.

27:07.860 --> 27:09.796
She's a Serving
Clearance Officer,

27:09.829 --> 27:11.297
and you don't know her.

27:11.330 --> 27:14.266
Clearance investigations are
my business too, Agent Ross.

27:14.300 --> 27:16.803
And a lot of requests
for Science funding

27:16.836 --> 27:18.738
come across my desk.

27:18.771 --> 27:21.107
One was for linen fabric.
A lot of it.

27:21.140 --> 27:22.408
Who requested it?

27:29.448 --> 27:31.383
[***]

27:35.121 --> 27:38.424
[INDISTINCT VOICES OVERLAPPING]

27:44.731 --> 27:45.898
[VOICES STOP]

27:45.932 --> 27:47.867
[GASPING]

27:51.804 --> 27:53.740
[PANTING]

27:56.342 --> 27:58.077
[SIGHS]

27:58.110 --> 28:00.046
[***]

28:02.248 --> 28:04.350
ROSS:
Honor, we're leaving.

28:08.387 --> 28:10.489
[FILM PROJECTOR HUMS]

28:10.522 --> 28:12.992
ROSS:
So the request for linen fabric

28:13.025 --> 28:15.094
came from a department
created to do research

28:15.127 --> 28:17.096
into Teep Prevention.

28:26.806 --> 28:29.141
They were using the Teeps
to their max in one lab.

28:29.175 --> 28:31.377
And in another, working out
how to stop them.

28:33.780 --> 28:34.914
[***]

28:46.425 --> 28:47.894
Who's that?

28:54.801 --> 28:57.003
ROSS:
Dr. Thaddeus Cutter.

28:57.036 --> 29:01.107
Resigned from the division
for health reasons 13 years ago.

29:01.140 --> 29:02.909
Rumor was he had
a breakdown.

29:05.044 --> 29:06.478
Something
on his mind, eh?

29:06.512 --> 29:09.015
Maybe a Teep could've read it.
Might've helped.

29:13.920 --> 29:15.354
Have to try it
on me sometime.

29:17.824 --> 29:19.826
I-it's okay.
I know you're forbidden

29:19.859 --> 29:21.060
to read an agent.

29:22.294 --> 29:23.462
You're different.

29:25.231 --> 29:28.200
You said that before.
How am I different?

29:28.234 --> 29:31.070
You asked if it
gets noisy in here.

29:31.103 --> 29:32.304
It does.

29:32.338 --> 29:35.842
The city's full
of stray thoughts.

29:35.875 --> 29:38.811
Sometimes I feel like
I'm a broken aerial,

29:38.845 --> 29:42.081
just picking up
all the chatter.

29:42.114 --> 29:44.817
And the grapevine
never stops. But...

29:47.353 --> 29:49.088
When I'm with you it's...

29:52.458 --> 29:54.060
quiet.

29:55.862 --> 29:56.996
[FILM BURNING]

29:59.131 --> 30:00.833
[GROANS]

30:02.101 --> 30:03.903
[***]

30:03.936 --> 30:07.306
* London's burning
London's burning *

30:07.339 --> 30:09.942
* Fetch the engines
Fetch the en-- *

30:09.976 --> 30:11.310
[CAR HONKS]

30:16.482 --> 30:18.150
[CAR HONKING]

30:21.087 --> 30:24.123
FRANKLYN:
Come on, Mary.
I'm sorry, ah?

30:24.156 --> 30:26.225
Don't walk away from me.

30:26.258 --> 30:31.063
[INDISTINCT VOICE ECHOING]

30:31.097 --> 30:32.464
Come out of the rain.

30:35.367 --> 30:37.870
That's a good girl.

30:37.904 --> 30:40.139
Where shall we go? Huh?

30:40.172 --> 30:42.074
[LAUGHS]
Where shall we go?

30:42.108 --> 30:43.642
[LAUGHS]

30:43.675 --> 30:45.044
Ah!

30:45.077 --> 30:46.212
Ugh!

30:48.114 --> 30:51.017
[GRUNTING]

30:51.050 --> 30:53.252
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

30:53.285 --> 30:57.123
* London's burning
London's burning *

30:57.156 --> 31:00.893
* Fetch the engines
Fetch the engines *

31:00.927 --> 31:04.630
* Fire, fire
Fire, fire *

31:04.663 --> 31:08.134
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

31:09.969 --> 31:13.139
Nobody leaves.
Don't let anyone out.

31:17.076 --> 31:19.211
There's riots. He'll do it.

31:19.245 --> 31:20.479
Some Teeps ambushed Franklyn.

31:20.512 --> 31:22.448
Some kind of mass attack
on his mind.

31:22.481 --> 31:24.383
He's talking like
my 4-year-old nephew now.

31:24.416 --> 31:26.185
Your wee fair
Mary's involved.

31:26.218 --> 31:28.687
MARY:
Honor, it's started.
Tell them all.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.589
Honor. Did you
hear what I said?

31:30.622 --> 31:32.258
Can you use
the Grapevine to find her?

31:32.291 --> 31:34.293
I don't know where she is.

31:34.326 --> 31:37.229
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

31:37.263 --> 31:39.165
They're arresting everyone
in your hostel.

31:39.198 --> 31:40.933
I can't stop them
getting to you.

31:40.967 --> 31:43.369
[BANGING ON CAR]

31:43.402 --> 31:46.605
TEEPS [WHISPERS OVERLAPPING]:
It's started. We have
to be strong.

31:46.638 --> 31:48.574
[BANGING ON CAR,
PEOPLE YELLING]

31:48.607 --> 31:50.342
Hear it?

31:50.376 --> 31:52.979
TEEPS [WHISPERS OVERLAPPING]:
Rise up. Fight back.

31:53.012 --> 31:54.613
Honor.

31:54.646 --> 31:57.616
TEEPS [WHISPERS OVERLAPPING]:
Here's the time for our attack.

31:57.649 --> 31:58.985
Honor.

32:01.520 --> 32:03.389
I have nowhere to go.

32:03.422 --> 32:05.357
[***]

32:07.293 --> 32:08.427
[ENGINE STARTS]

32:22.708 --> 32:24.043
[***]

32:39.525 --> 32:40.659
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

32:44.563 --> 32:46.698
[SOFT JAZZ
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

32:46.732 --> 32:48.967
This city is gonna explode.

32:51.037 --> 32:53.072
HONOR:
Normals want this.

32:53.105 --> 32:55.107
They want an excuse
to wipe us out.

32:55.141 --> 32:57.309
Maybe your friend
Mary thinks that.

32:57.343 --> 33:00.212
But you're with Clearance.
With me, right?

33:03.482 --> 33:05.517
Want a drink?

33:05.551 --> 33:07.319
I'm having one.

33:11.123 --> 33:13.659
Don't lump us all together.

33:17.396 --> 33:19.365
Could you trust me
on that, at least?

33:22.234 --> 33:24.170
How can I trust a man
who puts on jazz

33:24.203 --> 33:25.737
and pours me
a triple scotch?

33:27.273 --> 33:29.175
Oh, we agents can't date.

33:29.208 --> 33:31.077
No, too busy...

33:31.110 --> 33:32.611
probing each other
for weaknesses.

33:32.644 --> 33:34.213
Dinner becomes
interrogation.

33:34.246 --> 33:35.747
[LAUGHS]

33:35.781 --> 33:37.183
Teeps hate dating.

33:37.216 --> 33:38.650
I mean,
there's no mystery to it.

33:38.684 --> 33:42.788
We end up finishing
each other's sentences.

33:42.821 --> 33:44.690
We've got that in common.

33:55.467 --> 33:56.802
And you'd tell me, right?

33:56.835 --> 33:58.637
If you'd heard
of a Teep Underground.

34:00.439 --> 34:01.607
I'd take it in good faith.

34:01.640 --> 34:03.175
It wouldn't have
to come from you.

34:03.209 --> 34:04.476
And you'd tell me
what Normals

34:04.510 --> 34:06.345
are planning to do with us?

34:06.378 --> 34:07.546
If there was an uprising,

34:07.579 --> 34:09.681
what would happen
to the rest of us?

34:11.383 --> 34:12.551
If you don't trust me,

34:12.584 --> 34:14.120
read me.

34:17.223 --> 34:18.524
I don't want to.

34:18.557 --> 34:20.659
I'm giving you permission.

34:26.365 --> 34:29.401
I could read my mother's
thoughts in the womb.

34:29.435 --> 34:33.572
I mean, not words.
Just feeling.

34:36.208 --> 34:38.544
And I could read people
before I could read books.

34:38.577 --> 34:41.180
My parents hated me for it.

34:42.581 --> 34:44.750
Their fear was in my head
all the time.

34:48.887 --> 34:51.290
We make people afraid,
and we drive them away.

34:51.323 --> 34:52.758
And I don't want to dri--

34:55.927 --> 34:57.263
[GLASS SHATTERS]

35:10.376 --> 35:11.610
ROSS:
That's my dad.

35:12.744 --> 35:14.313
And he was an open book.

35:14.346 --> 35:16.415
Heart-on-sleeve guy.

35:16.448 --> 35:18.317
He was comfortable
in a room of Teeps

35:18.350 --> 35:20.352
because he wore it all
on the outside.

35:22.454 --> 35:24.723
[***]

35:24.756 --> 35:26.625
ROSS:
Anyone was welcome
to read my dad

35:26.658 --> 35:28.394
because he had
nothing to hide.

35:29.661 --> 35:32.231
And I loved him for that.

35:32.264 --> 35:33.865
You look happy.

35:35.701 --> 35:37.736
My happiest, actually.

35:39.405 --> 35:42.574
The sounds of the water...

35:42.608 --> 35:45.844
and the swish of the fly
as you present it to the trout.

35:45.877 --> 35:47.679
[SIGHS]
So you have to land it
just right.

35:47.713 --> 35:49.681
Otherwise,
they get the tickle.

35:49.715 --> 35:51.383
They know.
They get spooked.

35:52.784 --> 35:54.653
It's Zen, you know?

35:55.921 --> 35:57.789
Clears the mind.

36:00.392 --> 36:02.694
That's how my mind is
when I'm with you.

36:15.006 --> 36:16.675
That's easy enough
to read, right?

36:28.787 --> 36:31.690
[WATER TRICKLING]

36:39.831 --> 36:41.600
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

36:50.576 --> 36:51.743
[WATER SPLASHES]

36:51.777 --> 36:54.646
[***]

37:14.300 --> 37:15.634
[GASPS]

37:43.629 --> 37:44.930
[PAPERS RUSTLE]

37:49.968 --> 37:51.670
[GRUNTS]

37:51.703 --> 37:52.904
What are you doing?

37:52.938 --> 37:55.407
Looking for a new job
for you.

37:55.441 --> 37:57.509
You've slept with a Teep.
You're stuffed.

37:58.977 --> 38:00.846
We should elope.

38:00.879 --> 38:03.315
We could
go far away.

38:03.349 --> 38:04.583
To your river.

38:11.923 --> 38:13.625
If Cutter left
the Science Division

38:13.659 --> 38:15.494
because he wanted
to make hoods.

38:15.527 --> 38:17.863
He would have needed a supplier
for the linen.

38:17.896 --> 38:20.466
We've got nothing out of
those textile outlets.

38:20.499 --> 38:22.468
Yeah, but waxed linen
isn't just for clothing.

38:22.501 --> 38:24.002
It's also used
in the binding of books.

38:24.035 --> 38:25.471
[ROSS SIGHING]
And this place

38:25.504 --> 38:27.773
closed down 13 years ago.

38:30.008 --> 38:31.810
The Union Book Depository.

38:36.848 --> 38:38.083
No, you can't come with me.

38:38.116 --> 38:40.786
It's too dangerous
out there for a--

38:40.819 --> 38:42.654
For telepaths.

38:44.690 --> 38:47.359
Right, you'll be safe here.

38:47.393 --> 38:49.528
It's probably
a waste of time, anyway.

38:59.971 --> 39:01.907
[***]

39:04.743 --> 39:06.344
MARY:
Honor.

39:07.913 --> 39:09.815
Who is the Hood Maker?

39:12.551 --> 39:14.085
TEEP 1: Join us.
MARY: Honor.

39:14.119 --> 39:15.954
TEEP 2: Who is the hood maker?
MARY: Honor.

39:15.987 --> 39:17.155
Tell us.

39:17.188 --> 39:18.857
MARY:
Who is he?

39:18.890 --> 39:20.392
[VOICES OVERLAPPING]

39:20.426 --> 39:23.128
MARY: Who is he?
TEEP 3: Join us.

39:23.161 --> 39:25.697
MARY:
You can't betray us, Honor.

39:25.731 --> 39:28.467
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

39:36.442 --> 39:37.576
[HORN HONKS]

39:51.490 --> 39:53.625
[CAR ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

39:57.228 --> 39:59.965
[MECHANISM HUMMING]

40:15.246 --> 40:17.816
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

40:25.056 --> 40:26.625
[PAPER RUSTLING]

40:26.658 --> 40:28.093
[GUN CLICKS]

40:37.102 --> 40:39.738
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

40:54.185 --> 40:57.122
[JAZZ VOLUME INCREASES]

41:16.842 --> 41:18.777
[MUSIC STOPS]

41:59.084 --> 42:01.019
[PAPERS RUSTLING SOFTLY]

42:15.967 --> 42:18.570
[LIGHTS CLICKING ON]

42:18.604 --> 42:20.906
[MECHANISM HUMMING]

42:23.675 --> 42:26.277
I knew that somebody
would come, eventually.

42:26.311 --> 42:27.946
Well, I have
to congratulate you.

42:27.979 --> 42:30.949
Beast of an operation
you've got going on here.

42:30.982 --> 42:32.751
Why'd you have
those pictures of me,

42:32.784 --> 42:34.085
Dr. Cutter?

42:34.119 --> 42:36.955
Because I've always had
an interest in you,

42:36.988 --> 42:39.024
since I first met you.

42:39.057 --> 42:41.159
Met me?

42:41.192 --> 42:42.661
When?

42:42.694 --> 42:44.195
[CHUCKLES]

42:44.229 --> 42:46.865
In the old world I remember
how we fretted

42:46.898 --> 42:49.701
over the computers.
The web.

42:49.735 --> 42:52.270
The information on everyone
and everything.

42:52.303 --> 42:54.773
We built firewalls
and encrypted our lives.

42:54.806 --> 42:56.775
I always thought
it was an overreaction.

42:56.808 --> 42:58.209
There was a plug.
Pull it out. Off.

42:58.243 --> 42:59.611
Teeps don't have a plug.

42:59.645 --> 43:01.312
Exactly.

43:01.346 --> 43:05.951
The Union wanted a safeguard,
which is what I was developing.

43:05.984 --> 43:08.319
They wanted this firewall
for themselves,

43:08.353 --> 43:10.055
but it's too important.

43:10.088 --> 43:13.625
Protection should be democratic.
So should knowledge.

43:13.659 --> 43:14.960
And what about power?

43:14.993 --> 43:16.895
Because these things
are power.

43:16.928 --> 43:18.764
You can't hand
that kind of power to anyone.

43:18.797 --> 43:20.899
Why not?
We have the sanctity

43:20.932 --> 43:23.669
of our own thoughts
before the Teeps.

43:23.702 --> 43:27.939
Our minds are the only free,
independent states in existence.

43:27.973 --> 43:30.375
I get it. You see the Teeps
as an invading force.

43:30.408 --> 43:31.777
Now you want a war?

43:31.810 --> 43:34.846
No, an evolution.

43:34.880 --> 43:37.716
People can change
to counter the Teeps.

43:37.749 --> 43:39.718
Nature's balance.

43:39.751 --> 43:43.755
One day,
we'll make our own hoods.

43:43.789 --> 43:46.024
Maybe we already have,
Agent Ross.

43:48.827 --> 43:50.896
You're special.

43:50.929 --> 43:54.365
Oh, don't give me
those innocent eyes.

43:54.399 --> 43:58.870
You don't have to pretend.
I'm not your Teep partner.

43:58.904 --> 44:02.307
We both know what you can do.

44:02.340 --> 44:04.442
You're our new weapon
against them.

44:08.313 --> 44:11.883
[GRUNTS]
I'm being read.

44:11.917 --> 44:13.852
Jesus, Honor.
HONOR: What does he mean?

44:13.885 --> 44:16.021
Why are you a weapon?

44:16.054 --> 44:18.924
Nothing, it--
It doesn't mean anything.

44:18.957 --> 44:22.227
He's stalling.
Don't be so modest, Agent Ross.

44:22.260 --> 44:23.428
Tell her about your gift.

44:23.461 --> 44:24.830
That's enough, Cutter.

44:24.863 --> 44:26.397
What does he mean?

44:26.431 --> 44:29.467
CUTTER:
I mean that, quite frankly,
he's a weapon.

44:29.500 --> 44:31.402
Why?

44:33.872 --> 44:35.040
[FORCEFULLY]
Why?

44:35.073 --> 44:38.744
Read him and find out.

44:41.279 --> 44:42.413
[***]

45:18.283 --> 45:20.451
I can't.

45:20.485 --> 45:21.953
[CUTTER LAUGHS]

45:21.987 --> 45:24.089
He can block you.

45:24.122 --> 45:26.157
You can't get through.

45:29.828 --> 45:31.329
[GASPING]

45:35.967 --> 45:39.437
* London's burning
London's burning *

45:39.470 --> 45:44.009
* Fetch the engines
Fetch the engines *

45:44.042 --> 45:47.779
* Fire, fire
Fire, fire *

45:47.813 --> 45:49.781
[INDISTINCT SINGING IN DISTANCE]

45:52.283 --> 45:57.122
VOICE [WHISPERING]:
Get the Hood Maker.
Get the Hood Maker.

45:57.155 --> 45:58.289
Shit.

45:59.590 --> 46:01.326
She's led
them right to us.

46:01.359 --> 46:03.394
ROSS:
They're gonna tear you
to pieces, doctor.

46:03.428 --> 46:05.130
Is there another way out?

46:05.163 --> 46:07.132
Come on.
Don't.

46:07.165 --> 46:08.867
Out there,
through my office.

46:08.900 --> 46:10.468
It will take
you onto a fire escape.

46:10.501 --> 46:12.437
I'll distract them.
It's me they want anyway.

46:12.470 --> 46:13.872
ROSS:
No, you can't...

46:13.905 --> 46:15.173
MARY:
You can't betray us.

46:15.206 --> 46:17.843
You must be protected. Go.

46:19.911 --> 46:22.948
I was gonna tell you
when it was safe. Honor.

46:22.981 --> 46:24.449
[***]

46:24.482 --> 46:26.784
Honor! Honor!

46:28.219 --> 46:31.322
Open it.
Honor, open the door.

46:38.363 --> 46:41.466
We can make our own hoods.

46:59.150 --> 47:00.285
Honor, open the door.

47:02.053 --> 47:04.222
Honor.

47:04.255 --> 47:06.157
I had a talent.
I didn't understand it.

47:06.191 --> 47:08.626
They made me train.
They made me train, to--

47:08.659 --> 47:10.561
[CUTTER SCREAMING]

47:20.505 --> 47:22.607
[INDISTINCT MURMURING]

47:37.655 --> 47:39.590
[***]

47:54.039 --> 47:55.173
Fire, fire.

48:01.079 --> 48:02.513
Fire, fire.

48:06.084 --> 48:07.385
[ECHOING]
Fire, fire.

48:19.097 --> 48:20.231
Wait.

48:29.174 --> 48:30.708
I've no other
way out, Honor.

48:30.741 --> 48:32.377
You lied to me.

48:32.410 --> 48:33.644
We both lied, didn't we?

48:33.678 --> 48:35.981
You brought the Teeps here.
No.

48:36.014 --> 48:38.049
No, I didn't.
I couldn't stop that.

48:38.083 --> 48:39.584
We're all allowed to have
our secrets.

48:39.617 --> 48:42.187
That's our right.
Your right and mine.

48:42.220 --> 48:44.089
I didn't want
to hurt you, but--

48:44.122 --> 48:46.191
It wasn't my choice
to block you.

48:46.224 --> 48:49.094
You can't trust him, Honor.

48:49.127 --> 48:50.328
Then let me read you.

48:52.363 --> 48:53.631
I'll know the truth
if I read you.

49:06.344 --> 49:07.478
[***]

49:45.050 --> 49:47.152
HONOR [WHISPERING]:
Ross, let me through.

49:56.661 --> 49:57.995
ROSS:
Forgive me.

50:28.626 --> 50:31.362
OKHILE:
You're a major talent.

50:31.396 --> 50:33.798
Actually, you're a miracle.

50:33.831 --> 50:36.567
You're the only one we can risk
doing this with.

50:36.601 --> 50:40.538
Look at that fucking Teep.
Right in the inner sanctum.

50:42.507 --> 50:45.543
So you play partners
and keep her close.

50:45.576 --> 50:47.378
Cute for a mutant.

50:47.412 --> 50:49.580
Might run away with
the assignment, ma'am.

50:52.183 --> 50:56.354
Do whatever you have to,
to win her trust.

50:56.387 --> 50:58.523
Find out what the Teeps
are planning on the streets.

50:58.556 --> 51:00.191
Find whatever you can.

51:00.225 --> 51:02.593
I'll have it eating
out of the palm of my hand.

51:02.627 --> 51:05.830
Her. It's a her.

51:15.840 --> 51:18.243
ROSS:
Honor...

51:18.276 --> 51:19.410
[HONOR GASPS]

51:21.712 --> 51:23.648
I'm sorry, Honor.

51:26.484 --> 51:27.618
[CRYING]

51:32.323 --> 51:34.292
ROSS:
I did run away
with the assignment.

51:35.493 --> 51:36.794
I fell for you.

51:36.827 --> 51:38.796
[HONOR SIGHS]

51:38.829 --> 51:40.798
We can get out of the city.

51:42.633 --> 51:45.370
We can go to the mountains.

51:45.403 --> 51:47.338
You can read minds,
but you can't read my heart.

51:51.309 --> 51:52.477
Please, believe me, Honor.

51:56.847 --> 51:58.183
Please.

52:00.285 --> 52:01.786
I'm an open book now...

52:03.388 --> 52:05.923
just like my dad.

52:05.956 --> 52:07.658
You can trust me, Honor.

52:10.495 --> 52:11.862
Honor.

52:16.567 --> 52:18.236
Honor.

52:20.938 --> 52:22.607
[FORCEFULLY]
Honor.

52:26.711 --> 52:28.846
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

52:28.879 --> 52:31.749
Honor, we have
to trust each other.

52:31.782 --> 52:33.618
[CROWD SHOUTING]

52:33.651 --> 52:34.919
Or what hope is there?

52:40.691 --> 52:42.827
We can go far away.

52:45.563 --> 52:46.797
[FIRE CRACKLING]

52:53.238 --> 52:54.939
[***]
